<br>
as a little one in the Qeynos hills, I killed watchers by the dozens to afford my first set of real armor, and when I was finished, and had my full suit of banded armor . . .  well I may have been encumbered all the time, but everyone always admired my armor!  Some even called me a twink for having it!<br>
<br>
Nowadays at that level it is not uncommon to see people prancing about in a far superior mish mosh of armor including ivy! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I remember when the best bow you could craft was the mighty Shaped Darkwood Compound . . . . I should know! I made them by the dozen and sold them to aid in my fletching career for 500pp a bow!<br>
<br>
But Witht he discovery of Luclin we found a new god for our bows, a god called the Shaped Shadewood Compound. . .  and then later our wood elf bretherin found the Blessed Faydark Thunderbolt and the heart just went out of fletching for the common elf alltogether. . .<br>
<br>
But now my friends, now fletching for the common elf is back again wiht the discovery of planer crafted bows!  One of the top on that list being the Nightmarewood Compound! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I remember when the only way to move on from Qeynos to get to the bustling city of Freeport was to brave the Karanas, generaly not something you wanted to do unescorted!  Druids did not stick around Qeynos long enough to be able to get a teleport from them to a closer location, and niether did Wizzards, so your best bet was to hope to find a wizzard or druid in North Karana (if you made it that far) and wait for them at the huge wizzard Spires where it was safest.  If you couldnt not find a teleport from them to the western Commonlands, you sadly had to continue your dangerus treck on to Highpass, and if you didnt die in the Karanas, you were certain to do so in Highpas unescorted!<br>
<br>
Then! IF by some miracle you managed to get through the hold to the forest beyond, you had to wait untill daylight (if you can call it that in that murk) to pass through the dreaded wood, for at night there were horrers beyond your imagining just waiting for a ripe little traveler to stumble into thier realm.<br>
<br>
After that it gets not much better for a young traveler as you now have to cross the western Commonlands to get to the safer eastern commonlands and on to Freeport.<br>
<br>
Well nowadays freeport is just a book away!  Take a book to the Plane of Knowledge and on to freeport!  not one shred of danger involved!<br>
<br>
I remember trips to the Butcherblock Mountains to visit wiht the dwarvs being a tedius afair, a days long journey by boat, wiht a stop uncomfortably close to an island of seafuries!  I actualy remember one day, I had cast myself invisible for the trip so as not to be disturbed, and when we made that stop at the Sisters Island a seafury boarded the boat and killed all aboard but me!<br>
<br>
nowadays yet again, the mountains and thier dwarvs are but a planar book away . . . . .<br>
<br>
Do you know. . .  I think young travelers today are just spoiled in thier travels. . . . <p><table width="500" height="150" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
